261-71 Seaman Avenue, east side, between 215th and 218th, a newly completed apartment house.

1928.

Gelles Advertising Agency.

723180f-a.text:
Seaman Avenue, east side, between 215th and 218th Streets, just south of 261 Seaman Avenue, showing a rear view of 65-75 Park Terrace West. The wooden house, No. 65, with its annex, was built around 1905; the brick house immediately adjoining it is very new; the others were erected around 1920.

June 26, 1935.

P. L. Sperr.
